==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Farinose
<hw>Far`i*nose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>farinosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>farineux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Yielding farina; <as>as, <ex>farinose</ex>
substances</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>Covered with a sort of
white, mealy powder, as the leaves of some poplars, and the body of
certain insects; mealy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Farl</ent>⟦br⟧
